-- Express Kenya Says Its First-Half Profit Increased by 22% After Investment
-- Eric Ombok
-- 2010-07-29T04:52:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-29/express-kenya-says-first-half-profit-increased-by-22-after-investments.html

          
          
             Express Kenya Ltd., a transport
company, said first-half profit jumped 22 percent after the
company invested in new projects.  
 Net income rose to 30.9 million shillings ($383,348) in the
six months through June from 25.3 million shillings a year
earlier, the company said in a statement published in the
Nairobi-based Daily Nation newspaper today. Revenue fell 22
percent to 425.2 million shillings, it said.  
 “The directors are confident that the business strategies
put in place will maintain the consistency of growth in
profits,” Express Kenya said.  
